"Lithium-ion battery's life cycle count of 100+ charge-discharge cycles suggests it has been heavily used or has aged significantly; 'heavily used or aged' refers to a battery that has been through many charge-discharge cycles, which means the battery has been used extensively or is old.";

"A temperature of 30 degrees is considered high for the average operating temperature of a lithium-ion battery";

